SAW exits non-zero on this input by design — SHA-512's full
Merkle-Damgard chain uses Cryptol's parametric `Num#rec1` dispatch
over a polymorphic message length, surfacing as a `Prelude.fix`
that the L-5 lockdown refuses (and that L-1's `polymorphismResidual`
also flags via the `L@free : Num` residual). Phase 5 (recursion
design) does not lift this: the `Num#rec1` polymorphic-dispatch
shape is one of the explicit non-matched cases. Lifting requires
either upstream Cryptol-side specialization at the call site (fix
the message length before extraction) or a Phase 5 extension we
haven't designed.

Mirrors Rocq's `otherTests/saw-core-rocq/test_cryptol_module_sha512.log.good`
which pins the same shape as a clean refusal with diagnostic.
